        "id": 266820,
        "name": "Anonymous Pony",
        "username": "m4g1cp0ny",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/m4g1cp0ny/{size}/11506_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-04-23T22:52:16.191Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"goodec\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"68154\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/goodec/48/14726_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> goodec:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Recovery PIN</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>The issue with this is that the PIN is for much more than just recovery. It actually protects your data, etc.</p>\n<p>If this truly confuses people, I would probably change the UI to make it obvious that it’s not about a device PIN. How? Idk, don’t even remember what it looks like today, given I’ve disabled the reminders.</p>",
