        "id": 266838,
        "name": "Chris",
        "username": "goodec",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/goodec/{size}/14726_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-04-24T03:24:03.700Z",
        "cooked": "<p><em>Head tilt</em></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Your Signal PIN is a numeric or alphanumeric code used to help you <strong>recover your profile, settings, contacts, and block list</strong> if you ever lose or switch devices. It supports features like non-phone number based identifiers. A PIN can also serve as a registration lock.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Their support website is readily available -_-<br>\n<a href=\"https://support.signal.org/hc/en-us\" class=\"onebox\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">https://support.signal.org/hc/en-us</a></p>\n<p>The team can’t understand even the basics <strong>for</strong> some of you, so I really don’t know what you expect on the UI side if hairs are going to continue to be split poorly on what “Is” is and seemingly needing to add more than is necessary for labeling and redefine what ‘Recovery’ entails.</p>",
